'''''Episode I: Obi-Wan Kenobi''''' is a one-shot adaptation of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] told from the perspective of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]. The comic was written by [[Henry Gilroy]], illustrated by [[Martin Egeland]], and published by [[Dark Horse Comics]] on [[June 2]], [[1999]]. In [[2015]], ''Episode I: Obi-Wan Kenobi'' was digitally republished by [[Marvel Comics]] under the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] banner.

==Publisher's summary==
''Though all eyes are on the boy Anakin Skywalker, there is another young man making his rite of passage. The only thing standing between Obi-Wan Kenobi and Jedi Knighthood is a lesson he must learn from his Jedi Master, but the only place where he can learn that lesson is in the middle of an intergalactic war!''<ref name="Dark Horse" />

